v3.0.5: remove zeroAccess bash check (matches Miessler original)

Per danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure SecurityValidator.hook.ts,
bash commands are validated ONLY with regex patterns (bashToolPatterns).
zeroAccessPaths should only apply to file operations (read/write/edit).

The bash zeroAccess check was a pi-pai addition that caused false positives
on substrings like process dot env, Object dot keys, pi-envman, etc.